(756, 41, '# BMSE3014 Software Maintenance\n\n## Chapter 2: Taxonomy of Software Maintenance\n\n### Key Characteristics of Maintenance Activities\n\n*   Keeping an eye on the software\'s day-to-day operations\n*   Keeping software changes under control\n*   Improve the software\'s current functions\n*   Threats to security are identified, and security flaws are fixed\n*   Preventing software performance from deteriorating to unacceptable levels\n\nSource: http://swebokwiki.org/Chapter_5:_Software_Maintenance\n\n### Characteristics of Software Maintenance\n\n#### Constraints of an Existing System\n\nOn an operational system, maintenance is carried out. As a result, all changes must be compatible with the existing software architecture, design, and code limitations.\n\n#### Shorter Time Frame\n\nMaintenance activities might last anywhere from a few hours to many months, but software creation can take up to a year.\n\n#### Available Test Data', '[0.009807014,0.040722363,-0.031148702,-0.002991705,-0.020332403,0.027707176,0.07214815,0.046747454,-0.026022984,-0.0037611858,0.009944416,0.041482434,0.06949167,-0.019795492,0.032743163,-0.020099485,0.063493796,0.07859255,-0.026131844,-0.03054047,-0.00923248,-0.020219825,-0.053006712,-0.06553273,-0.036650777,-0.06182653,0.072207905,0.022823706,0.017043022,-0.04948387,0.0156150395,0.017037733,0.00083068013,-0.01919761,0.040158566,0.029900245,0.014065349,0.022085149,-0.03397719,-0.051472995,-0.04465381,-0.052092932,-0.04426667,0.057101235,-0.06647235,0.036677342,-0.015259297,-0.02957533,-0.03973627,0.015849184,0.016859807,0.011080133,-0.021105172,0.043407463,-0.045378745,-0.064624615,-0.018826433,-0.058834355,0.006676405,-0.042565305,0.004595091,-0.030425698,0.007354056,-0.044917755,-0.013615915,-0.000459737,-0.024804113,-0.03550955,-0.039117295,-0.018991493,-0.027952971,0.06654557,-0.077176556,-0.004008212,0.048286304,-0.06801983,-0.013436979,-0.02588152,-0.03752316,0.01372621,-0.0043926435,0.017102499,0.03151965,0.008306987,0.0