(757, 41, 'gn, and code limitations.\n\n#### Shorter Time Frame\n\nMaintenance activities might last anywhere from a few hours to many months, but software creation can take up to a year.\n\n#### Available Test Data\n\nTest cases are created from scratch during software development, however software maintenance can choose a portion of these test cases and run them as regression tests. As a result, selecting acceptable test cases from the existing test suite is a hurdle. To effectively test the code changes, in addition to the regression test cases, new test cases must be written.\n\n### Intention-Based Classification\n\nAccording to ISO/IEC 14764, the categories of software maintenance are:\n\n*   Corrective\n*   Adaptive\n*   Perfective\n*   Preventive\n\nSource: http://swebokwiki.org/Chapter_5:_Software_Maintenance\n\n#### Corrective Maintenance\n\nReact to problems that are uncovered. Unplanned (unscheduled) software maintenance is also required to allow the software to function.\n\nSource: http://swebokwiki.', '[-0.0037857413,0.002609109,-0.00481263,0.030638073,-0.024043282,0.01908052,0.05180469,0.056755286,-0.019074874,-0.021324774,-0.020649882,0.028199239,0.07166323,-0.013489284,0.0045672744,-0.013497798,0.06260941,0.011235239,-0.070830554,0.00079092704,0.02040278,-0.029324604,-0.049254395,-0.05843391,-0.045440316,-0.03486722,0.055340484,0.018938435,-0.01690107,-0.043146573,0.015761552,0.051835794,0.03617988,-0.009182671,0.06677149,0.026805354,0.043572795,0.016636245,-0.033751503,-0.008685347,-0.044531938,-0.048549738,-0.04094135,0.041268542,-0.058014583,0.0113490755,0.011220892,0.006736131,0.0059063616,0.039125305,0.026356291,0.028827375,0.022690201,0.04461606,-0.016475566,-0.042287953,-0.0138118835,-0.030628622,0.03272931,0.0017953418,0.03260843,-0.03665925,-0.009890217,0.015157713,-0.0013676652,0.0005746822,-0.049287137,-0.041627195,-0.0691123,-0.015182423,-0.011898509,0.011156845,-0.061250437,-0.0030958818,0.027104022,-0.027173303,-0.0035409546,-0.04080499