(758, 41, 'tenance\n\n#### Corrective Maintenance\n\nReact to problems that are uncovered. Unplanned (unscheduled) software maintenance is also required to allow the software to function.\n\nSource: http://swebokwiki.org/Chapter_5:_Software_Maintenance\n\n#### Adaptive Maintenance\n\nMaintain software usability in an ever-changing environment. For example, software modifications may be required as a result of an operating system upgrade.\n\nSource: http://swebokwiki.org/Chapter_5:_Software_Maintenance\n\n#### Perfective Maintenance\n\nThe goal is to increase user experience, processing efficiency, and maintainability, among other things. For a better user experience, the program outputs can be made more understandable; the program can be updated to make it faster, hence enhancing processing efficiency.\n\nSource: http://swebokwiki.org/Chapter_5:_Software_Maintenance\n\n#### Preventive Maintenance', '[0.043349944,0.005289989,-0.02722447,-0.010411581,-0.018340033,0.007650459,0.062965974,0.06403808,0.018924173,-0.057011455,-0.026930278,0.0461869,0.042492907,-0.030640991,0.043136936,0.0070437593,0.07153584,0.011343372,-0.06681322,-0.028355712,-0.0043689464,-0.016118778,-0.06432162,-0.07532713,-0.026222289,-0.041321777,0.064962685,-0.0153669715,-0.01734872,-0.026328532,0.058717214,0.0411024,0.030871859,-0.0344983,0.043003514,0.054449685,-0.014042535,0.007552454,-0.02054078,-0.022663558,-0.039721306,-0.061647944,-0.051480513,0.036691118,-0.022415208,0.039954092,0.005584263,0.04838304,0.008333813,-0.005701912,-0.015776236,-0.019967847,-0.030618168,0.01437831,-0.022966996,-0.059148315,-0.05792751,-0.017590985,0.0054845833,-0.025555532,-0.034018178,0.002826973,0.018371373,-0.021705097,0.01780757,0.015959011,-0.08700389,-0.03930298,-0.034833476,-0.056349654,-0.017436992,0.018477334,-0.055912394,-0.009617392,0.005766074,-0.021699155,-0.003923448,-0.045703303,-0.0032891806,0.033566322,0.031449355,0.027605236,0.048437145,0.021359505,0.023278283,-0.027057303,-0.005673971,-0.09967