(775, 41, 'hy, P., Naik K. (2014). Software Evolution and Maintenance – A Practitioner’s Approach. John Wiley and Son. Springer Vieweg.\n\n## Maintenance Models\n\n### Reuse-Oriented Models\n\n1.  Quick fix model\n2.  Iterative enhancement model\n3.  Full reuse model\n\nSource: Tripathy, P., Naik K. (2014). Software Evolution and Maintenance – A Practitioner’s Approach. John Wiley and Son. Springer Vieweg.\n\n### Reuse-Oriented Models\n\nAssumes that existing components can be re-used in software maintenance. It consists of the following steps:\n\n*   Identifying the components of the old system which can be reused\n*   Understanding these components\n*   Modifying the old system components so that they can be used in the new system\n*   Integrating the modified components into the new system.\n\nSource: http://www.professionalqa.com/software-maintenance-models\nSource: Tripathy, P., Naik K. (2014). Software Evolution and Maintenance – A Practitioner’s Approach. John Wiley and Son. Springer Vieweg.', '[-0.011421826,0.015603571,0.00092915725,-0.0056735836,0.043040443,-0.008070391,0.03469622,0.05226863,-0.018667324,-0.03167719,-0.038484618,0.06702695,0.044459127,0.0029257094,0.02960728,-0.0069828727,0.069652654,0.040357057,-0.053270265,-0.024411399,0.015011223,0.0025693602,-0.05394029,-0.045459416,-0.0059172893,-0.036235552,0.06797733,0.00313409,-0.0052513764,-0.027525013,0.01535174,0.04377158,0.023883516,-0.027502237,0.022776183,0.045991175,-0.0067811315,0.01987942,-0.030538324,0.0016772774,-0.048441526,-0.021871762,-0.022345452,0.013810619,-0.0033816101,-0.00035569913,0.02884516,0.026752407,-0.048436575,0.0011037352,0.032056373,-0.007110973,-0.026980018,0.03232061,-0.03471974,-0.039667085,-0.044839352,0.015921608,-0.010144307,-0.011511435,0.02848467,-0.009347927,-0.020351827,-0.02916886,0.03243238,-0.0057044905,-0.09749016,-0.011694365,-0.10856979,-0.058642168,-0.028459696,0.053552933,-0.072288156,0.018623456,0.01088067,-0.056819335,0.0031354674,-0.0564887,-0.010175