(28, 33, 'MCQ', '[{\"question\":\"According to the course structure for BMSE3014, what percentage of the final grade is the exam worth?\",\"answer\":\"40%\",\"options\":[\"60%\",\"40%\",\"50%\",\"100%\"]},{\"question\":\"What is software evolution primarily concerned with?\",\"answer\":\"The ongoing enhancement of software after its initial release.\",\"options\":[\"The initial design phase of a new application.\",\"The ongoing enhancement of software after its initial release.\",\"Deleting old software to make room for new versions.\",\"The process of marketing software to new users.\"]},{\"question\":\"Based on the IEEE Standard definition, what is software maintenance?\",\"answer\":\"Modifying a software system after delivery to correct faults or improve performance.\",\"options\":[\"The initial process of writing code for a new application.\",\"Selling a software product to another company.\",\"Modifying a software system after delivery to correct faults or improve performance.\",\"The act of training new users on how to use the software.\"]},{\"question\":\"What is a key difference between software development and software maintenance?\",\"answer\":\"Development is requirements-driven, while maintenance is event-driven.\",\"options\":[\"Development is requirements-driven, while maintenance is event-driven.\",\"Development is event-driven, while maintenance is requirements-driven.\",\"Development is only done by senior engineers.\",\"Maintenance does not involve writing any new code.\"]},{\"question\":\"What two teams does the DevOps methodology primarily aim to integrate?\",\"answer\":\"Development (Dev) and IT Operations (Ops)\",\"options\":[\"Marketing and Sales\",\"Human Resources and Finance\",\"Development (Dev) and IT Operations (Ops)\",\"Legal and Compliance\"]},{\"question\":\"What is the fundamental DevOps principle that holds developers responsible for the deployment and ongoing maintenance of their code?\",\"answer\":\"The \\\"you build it, you own it\\\" philosophy\",\"options\":[\"The Agile Manifesto\",\"The waterfall model\",\"Continuous Integration\",\"The \\\"you build it, you own it\\\" philosophy\"]},{\"question\":\"Which of the following is listed as a reason for performing software maintenance?\",\"answer\":\"To fix discovered software bugs.\",\"options\":[\"To decrease the software\'s usability.\",\"To prevent users from getting new features.\",\"To fix discovered software bugs.\",\"To make the software incompatible with new devices.\"]}]'),
(29, 34, 'Short Question', '[{\"question\":\"According to the SEI\'s working definition, software sustainment encompasses more than just technical procedures. What five distinct, non-technical and technical elements are required to fully support, maintain, and operate a system\'s software aspects?\",\"answer\":\"The five elements are processes, procedures, people, material, and information.\"},{\"question\":\"Based on Mehdi Jazayeri\'s quote and the principles of software maintenance costs, explain the relationship between the evolution of knowledge about a system and the significant increase in maintenance costs during its later life cycle stages.\",\"answer\":\"As our knowledge about the software and its environment evolves (per Jazayeri), user demands for new functionalities and adaptations increase. This growing complexity, coupled with addressing latent faults, leads to more intricate and costly maintenance modifications later in the software\'s life.\"},{\"question\":\"What specific financial and administrative roadblock, as identified by Lapham & Sei (2014), can prevent a fully developed and tested software system from officially entering the sustainment phase?\",\"answer\":\"The lack of allocated funding for the creation and negotiation of the Sustainment Transition Plan.\"},{\"question\":\"While both software development and maintenance can involve coding, what is the fundamental difference in their respective \'drivers\' that shapes their entire process initiation and workflow?\",\"answer\":\"Software development is \'requirements driven,\' beginning with the objective to build a system for specific functionalities, whereas software maintenance is \'event driven,\' initiated in response to specific occurrences like bug reports, security threats, or update requests.\"},{\"question\":\"The DevOps movement promotes a \'you build it, you own it\' philosophy to improve software maintenance. According to the text, what is the primary cultural limitation this movement has faced despite successfully integrating development and operations teams?\",\"answer\":\"While DevOps has successfully connected developers with maintenance responsibilities, it has not yet managed to make the maintenance tasks themselves as culturally valued or appealing as the work of coding and developing new features.\"},{\"question\":\"In the context of the DevOps life-cycle, what strategic approach is enabled by the heavy use of automated and continuous testing, and what is its main advantage?\",\"answer\":\"The approach is known as \'shift-left,\' which integrates testing much earlier in the development pipeline. Its primary advantage is the early detection and resolution of issues, which is more cost-effective and efficient than finding them post-deployment.\"},{\"question\":\"What are three distinct challenges outlined by Lapham & Sei (2014) that are specific to the sustainment of Commercial Off-The-Shelf (COTS) software, beyond general maintenance issues?\",\"answer\":\"Challenges specific to COTS software include managing system obsolescence, handling technology updates from the vendor, securing source code through escrow, and managing vendor license agreements.\"}]'),
(30, 35, 'MCQ', '[{\"question\":\"According to ISO\\/IEC 14764, which of the following are the four main categories of software maintenance?\",\"answer\":\"Corrective, Adaptive, Perfective, Preventive\",\"options\":[\"Corrective, Adaptive, Perfective, Preventive\",\"Enhancive, Reductive, Groomative, Updative\",\"Proactive, Reactive, Corrective, Enhancive\",\"Analysis, Design, Implementation, Testing\"]},{\"question\":\"Which type of maintenance is performed to keep software usable in a changing environment, such as after an operating system upgrade?\",\"answer\":\"Adaptive Maintenance\",\"options\":[\"Corrective Maintenance\",\"Adaptive Maintenance\",\"Perfective Maintenance\",\"Preventive Maintenance\"]},{\"question\":\"What is the primary goal of Perfective Maintenance?\",\"answer\":\"To increase user experience, processing efficiency, and maintainability\",\"options\":[\"To fix bugs and uncovered problems\",\"To adapt the software to a new environment\",\"To increase user experience, processing efficiency, and maintainability\",\"To find and fix flaws before they become operational problems\"]},{\"question\":\"Which maintenance activity involves reacting to problems that are uncovered and is typically unplanned?\",\"answer\":\"Corrective Maintenance\",\"options\":[\"Adaptive Maintenance\",\"Perfective Maintenance\",\"Preventive Maintenance\",\"Corrective Maintenance\"]},{\"question\":\"According to the text, what percentage of total software development costs does software maintenance typically consume?\",\"answer\":\"60% to 80%\",\"options\":[\"10% to 20%\",\"25% to 40%\",\"40% to 50%\",\"60% to 80%\"]},{\"question\":\"Which software maintenance model is described as low cost and having less concern for the impacts of modifications?\",\"answer\":\"Quick fix model\",\"options\":[\"Iterative enhancement model\",\"Full reuse model\",\"Quick fix model\",\"Boehm\'s model\"]},{\"question\":\"In the IEEE 1219 Maintenance Process, which attribute refers to the items that are measured during the execution of an activity?\",\"answer\":\"Metrics\",\"options\":[\"Input\",\"Output\",\"Control\",\"Metrics\"]}]');

